---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Mail } from 'lucide-react';
---

<Layout title="About - Henrik's home">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 pt-6 sm:pt-16 pb-16 max-w-5xl">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="mb-16 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 100ms">About Me</h1>
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-6 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 200ms">
          I'm an AI software composer focused on building and shipping products that make a difference.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Journey Section -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 sm:mb-6">My Journey</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 400ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üöÄ</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">The Teaching Years</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Spent 20+ years in the classroom, teaching middle school science. 
              Loved breaking down complex topics for students and watching those 
              "aha!" moments. Always been the tech-savvy teacher who could fix 
              the projector or help colleagues with their laptops.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 500ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üíº</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">The AI Awakening</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              When ChatGPT dropped, I saw it as more than just another tech trend. 
              Started using it to create lesson plans and learning materials. 
              That's when I realized - this technology could help people way 
              beyond the classroom.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 600ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üí°</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">The Pivot</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Took the scariest leap of my life in 2023. Started learning to code 
              with AI as my co-pilot. Turns out explaining complex topics to 13-year-olds 
              prepared me perfectly for breaking down technical challenges into 
              manageable pieces.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 700ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üéØ</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">Now</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Building AI-powered tools that help other career-changers and non-techies 
              harness the power of AI. Because if a middle school teacher can do this, 
              anyone can. Sometimes the best innovations come from outsider perspectives.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Skills & Expertise -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 sm:mb-6 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 800ms">Skills & Expertise</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 900ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üéì</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">Teaching + Tech</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Years of breaking down complex topics into digestible pieces makes me 
              great at explaining tech stuff to non-techies. Plus, I've got the 
              patience of someone who's dealt with middle schoolers for two decades.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 1000ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üåü</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">My Approach</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              I believe in making tech accessible to everyone. AI isn't just for 
              programmers - it's for teachers, artists, small business owners, and 
              anyone willing to learn. Sometimes the best person to build tools 
              is someone who knows the struggle.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 1100ms">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üõ†Ô∏è</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 subheading">The Toolbox</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Started with zero coding knowledge but now comfortable with web development 
              basics. My real superpower is combining ChatGPT, Midjourney, and other AI 
              tools to build useful stuff. Currently learning whatever helps me bring my 
              ideas to life.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Get in Touch -->
    <section class="mb-8 sm:mb-12">
      <div class="bg-muted/50 border rounded-lg p-8 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 1200ms">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-xl animate-bounce-once">üëã</span>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Let's Connect</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
              Whether you want to discuss a project, share ideas, or just say hi, I'd love to hear from you.
            </p>
            <Button asChild>
              <a href="mailto:your@email.com" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
                Get in Touch
                <Mail className="w-4 h-4" />
              </a>
            </Button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Add fade-up animation */
  .animate-fade-up {
    animation: fadeUp 0.5s ease-out forwards;
  }

  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { 
      opacity: 0; 
      transform: translateY(20px);
    }
    to { 
      opacity: 1; 
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  /* Add bounce animation for emojis */
  .animate-bounce-once {
    animation: bounce 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.36, 0, 0.66, -0.56) 500ms;
    animation-iteration-count: 1;
  }

  @keyframes bounce {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
    50% { transform: translateY(-25%); }
  }
</style> 